    {
      "id": "-qn8ROcrFh-36nRxeApX2",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 228,
      "y": 230.5,
      "width": 623.9796142578125,
      "height": 2200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "beM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1599324236,
      "version": 1457,
      "versionNonce": 709965812,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1783258241081,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Questions:\n\nq. imp features?\nUser searches a location\ngets point A to B routes\nselectes a route and sees navigation with ETA\ngets live traffic updates\nre-route based on traffic conditions\n\nq. scale\n1 billion DAU\n\nq. how do we get raw data?\nprecomputes and raw data given\n\nq. Multiple locations\nno\n\nq. search along route\nno\n\nq. buiness info?\nno\n\nq. different travel modes?\nyes, drive, ride and walk\n\n\nFunctional req:\nUser searches a location\ngets point A to B routes\nselectes a route and sees navigation with ETA\ngets live traffic updates\nre-route based on traffic conditions\n\nNFR:\nScalability\nAvailability : 99.99\nlow latency\nREliable and fault tolerant\n\nBack of the envelope calculations:\n\nStorage\n1. Map of the world\n2. routng tile info\n3. metadata\n\n1. map of the world\nmap tiles at different zoom level\n0 | 1\n1 | 4\n2 | 16\n...\n20 | ~1.1 trillion\n21 | ~4.4 trillion\n\n4.4 trillion * 100 kb per tile = 4.1 * 10^12 * 100 kb\n= 440 pb\nabout 90% of the world is unhabited\nso 440 * 10% = ~50 pb\nat each zoom level = ~100 pb\n\n2. routing tiles\nrequirement said tbs of raw data, we convert it to routing tiles\n\n4 trillion * 100 kb = 50 pb\n\n3. metadata\n4.4 trillion * 24 bytes = 120 tb \n\nTraffic\n1 billion DAU \n\nQuery for navigation\n1 billion * 2 \n= 2 * 10^9 / 10^5\n= 20000 rps\n\nReal time location capture\n1 billion DAU * 30 mins a day\n= 30 billion mins a day\n= 30 b * 60 secs / 10^5\n= 1800 * 10^9 / 10^5\n= 18 * 10^6 updates per second\n= batch req and upadte every 10 second\n= 1,800,000 updates per second\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Questions:\n\nq. imp features?\nUser searches a location\ngets point A to B routes\nselectes a route and sees navigation with ETA\ngets live traffic updates\nre-route based on traffic conditions\n\nq. scale\n1 billion DAU\n\nq. how do we get raw data?\nprecomputes and raw data given\n\nq. Multiple locations\nno\n\nq. search along route\nno\n\nq. buiness info?\nno\n\nq. different travel modes?\nyes, drive, ride and walk\n\n\nFunctional req:\nUser searches a location\ngets point A to B routes\nselectes a route and sees navigation with ETA\ngets live traffic updates\nre-route based on traffic conditions\n\nNFR:\nScalability\nAvailability : 99.99\nlow latency\nREliable and fault tolerant\n\nBack of the envelope calculations:\n\nStorage\n1. Map of the world\n2. routng tile info\n3. metadata\n\n1. map of the world\nmap tiles at different zoom level\n0 | 1\n1 | 4\n2 | 16\n...\n20 | ~1.1 trillion\n21 | ~4.4 trillion\n\n4.4 trillion * 100 kb per tile = 4.1 * 10^12 * 100 kb\n= 440 pb\nabout 90% of the world is unhabited\nso 440 * 10% = ~50 pb\nat each zoom level = ~100 pb\n\n2. routing tiles\nrequirement said tbs of raw data, we convert it to routing tiles\n\n4 trillion * 100 kb = 50 pb\n\n3. metadata\n4.4 trillion * 24 bytes = 120 tb \n\nTraffic\n1 billion DAU \n\nQuery for navigation\n1 billion * 2 \n= 2 * 10^9 / 10^5\n= 20000 rps\n\nReal time location capture\n1 billion DAU * 30 mins a day\n= 30 billion mins a day\n= 30 b * 60 secs / 10^5\n= 1800 * 10^9 / 10^5\n= 18 * 10^6 updates per second\n= batch req and upadte every 10 second\n= 1,800,000 updates per second\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
